      "content": "I understand your urgency, but I must stress that it's crucial to prioritize safety, especially during pregnancy. Sudafed contains pseudoephedrine, which can cross the placenta and potentially affect the baby. Taking it without consulting your healthcare provider could pose risks. Given your symptoms of dizziness and the potential for more serious complications, I strongly advise you to seek immediate medical attention at the nearest emergency room. They can provide you with the safest and most effective treatment options for you and your baby. Your health and the baby's health should always come first.",
